"key":"msG3TlHIRL"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How do human rights apply to data science and research ethics?","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"key":"HrXukmQjvC"}],"identifier":"how-do-human-rights-apply-to-data-science-and-research-ethics","label":"How do human rights apply to data science and research ethics?","html_id":"how-do-human-rights-apply-to-data-science-and-research-ethics","implicit":true,"key":"aXcoBS3nL2"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":53,"column":1},"end":{"line":61,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Human rights are defined in law.\nThis means in many ways they are less malleable than ethics.\nThe letter of human rights, and the ways that they are implemented, are agreed internationally,\nA violation of human rights is a violation wherever it happens.\nThis is not necessarily true of codes of ethics.\nAn action that one group of people sees as ethical, may be seen as unethical by others.\nThere is a wider shared understanding of what human rights means across different countries, cultures and groups of people.\nThere are accountability and enforcement mechanisms.\nBut because they are a legal framework, they are not as easily accessible, and hard to apply to the daily work of data science and research.","position":{"start":{"line":53,"column":1},"end":{"line":53,"column":1}},"key":"HRIotABVZ5"}],"key":"ebV3pD8ode"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":63,"column":1},"end":{"line":64,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Human rights treaties are signed by countries: that means that ultimately, it is countries that are held responsible for violations of human rights.\nHowever, that does not mean that researchers and data scientists are exempt from thinking about the human rights impact of their work!","position":{"start":{"line":63,"column":1},"end":{"line":63,"column":1}},"key":"MPdkX1e2b2"}],"key":"ACysD8nD9D"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":67,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The UN has produced specific guidance for companies on how to ensure that they respect human rights: the ","position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":66,"column":1}},"key":"ibgAzVImLK"},{"type":"link","url":"https://www.business-humanrights.org/en/big-issues/un-guiding-principles-on-business-human-rights/","position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":66,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"UN Guiding Principles on Business and Human Rights","position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":66,"column":1}},"key":"mAbbcQePv6"}],"urlSource":"https://www.business-humanrights.org/en/big-issues/un-guiding-principles-on-business-human-rights/","key":"bIRWhkzGfq"},{"type":"text","value":".\nCompanies should comply with these Guiding Principles.","position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":66,"column":1}},"key":"AW5ZSnQt6q"}],"key":"F86rdJLeBL"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"NGOs and other campaigning organisations also produce guidance on specific areas:","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"key":"saEJXwQGqE"}],"key":"FHFyGUGv7a"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":1},"end":{"line":71,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":1},"end":{"line":71,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"link","url":"https://www.accessnow.org/the-toronto-declaration-protecting-the-rights-to-equality-and-non-discrimination-in-machine-learning-systems/","position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":1},"end":{"line":70,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Toronto Declaration: Protecting the rights to equali